# ResumeIQ — AI-Powered Resume Analyzer

An intelligent dual-mode resume analysis application built with 
LangChain, ChromaDB, and Groq (Llama 3.1) that serves both job 
seekers and hiring managers.

## What It Does

**Recruiter Mode** — Upload multiple resumes against one job description to get:
- Ranked candidate list by match score
- Strengths and gaps per candidate
- Side-by-side comparison table
- Exportable results

**Candidate Mode** — Upload your resume and a job description to get:
- ATS compatibility score (0-100)
- Missing skills and keywords
- Bullet point rewrites in XYZ format
- Personalized improvement suggestions

## Architecture

This application uses Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) to ground 
LLM responses in expert hiring knowledge rather than relying on 
general training data.

Knowledge Base (ATS rules, FAANG guides, bullet examples)
↓
LangChain Text Splitter + HuggingFace Embeddings
↓
ChromaDB Vector Store
↓
LangChain Retriever → Groq LLM (Llama 3.1)
↓
FastAPI Backend → Streamlit Frontend

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|------------|
| Framework | LangChain |
| LLM | Groq — Llama 3.1 (free) |
| Vector Database | ChromaDB |
| Embeddings | HuggingFace sentence-transformers |
| Backend | FastAPI |
| Frontend | Streamlit |
| Language | Python 3.14 |

## Project Structure
resumeiq/
├── app/
│   ├── main.py              # FastAPI endpoints
│   ├── parser.py            # PDF text extraction
│   ├── embedder.py          # HuggingFace embeddings
│   ├── scorer.py            # Groq LLM scoring
│   ├── candidate_mode.py    # Candidate analysis logic
│   └── recruiter_mode.py    # Recruiter ranking logic
├── knowledge_base/
│   ├── ingestor.py          # RAG pipeline
│   ├── ats_rules.txt        # ATS optimization rules
│   ├── faang_guide.txt      # FAANG resume guidelines
│   └── bullet_examples.txt  # Strong vs weak bullet examples
├── frontend/
│   └── streamlit_app.py     # Streamlit UI
├── tests/
│   └── test_*.py            # Unit tests
├── .env.example             # Environment variables template
└── requirements.txt         # Project dependencies

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites
- Python 3.14
- Groq API key (free at console.groq.com)

### Installation
```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/resumeiq.git
cd resumeiq

# Create virtual environment
python3 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate  # Mac/Linux

# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Set up environment variables
cp .env.example .env
# Add your GROQ_API_KEY to .env
```

### Run the App
```bash
# Start FastAPI backend
uvicorn app.main:app --reload

# In a new terminal, start Streamlit frontend
streamlit run frontend/streamlit_app.py
```

Open `http://localhost:8501` in your browser.

## API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| GET | `/health` | Health check |
| POST | `/analyze/candidate` | Analyze single resume |
| POST | `/analyze/recruiter` | Rank multiple resumes |

## Why RAG?

Standard LLM resume feedback is generic. By building a RAG pipeline 
over curated hiring knowledge (ATS rules, FAANG-specific guides, 
bullet point examples), the feedback is grounded in expert knowledge 
rather than general training data — producing significantly more 
accurate and actionable results.

## Future Improvements
- Add support for DOCX resume format
- Integrate LinkedIn job scraper for automatic JD ingestion
